text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia improcera is a shrub belonging to the genus Acacia and the subgenus Phyllodineae. It is native to an area in the Goldfields-Esperance region of Western Australia.The spreading spiny shrub typically grows to a height of 0.15 to 0.4 metres (0.5 to 1.3 ft) and produces yellow flowers in August.
